 THE PILOT REPORTED THAT HE WAS FLYING THE AIRPLANE AROUND THE PATTERN 
TO WARM UP THE OIL IN PREPARATION FOR AN ANNUAL INSPECTION. JUST PRIOR 
TO THE FLIGHT, A RAIN STORM HAD PASSED OVER THE AREA AND THE DIRT STRIP 
WAS WET. DURING THE LANDING ROLL, THE RIGHT MAIN LANDING GEAR SANK IN 
THE MUD. THE PILOT APPLIED THE LEFT BRAKE HARD AND THE AIRPLANE NOSED 
OVER. 
 UNSUITABLE TERRAIN WAS SELECTED FOR LANDING. A FACTOR TO THE ACCIDENT 
WAS: SOFT TERRAIN. 
